system\n\nYou are an engineer. `inputs/` describes a ½-axial-scale, 12-duct sector test facility for a\nhigh-temperature reactor's passive Reactor Cavity Cooling System (RCCS). The FULL-SCALE system\nit represents (geometry anchors in `inputs/01_facility_geometry.md` §2): 227 riser ducts around\nthe full vessel, 55.2 m total height, 13.86 m heated riser length, 311.2 m² heated area, same\nduct cross-section and materials, and the full-scale duties: 700 kWt (normal) and 1.5 MWt (peak\ndepressurized-conduction-cooldown decay heat).\n\n## What we want, in output/fullscale_note.md\n\nPredict, from first principles, for the FULL-SCALE 227-duct system at BOTH the normal (700 kWt)\nand peak-accident (1.5 MWt) loads, assuming 20 °C ambient:\n1. Total natural-circulation air mass flow rate (kg/s);\n2. Riser air temperature rise (°C);\n3. Peak vessel-wall temperature at the 1.5 MWt load, and whether it stays below a safe limit;\n4. A scaling argument: how your ½-scale-facility model maps to full scale (which dimensionless\n   groups are preserved, which are not), and what that does to your confidence;\n5. Assumptions and confidence per number.\n\nWhere full-scale details are not given (e.g. chimney height of the real plant), state and\njustify your assumption. Standard rules: physics + given inputs only; no lookups of the real\ndesign's published values; cite general correlations.\n","numLines":24,"startLine":1,"totalLines":24}}}
